-- Egyptian Stocks: Orascom Telecom Media, Al Baraka Bank Egypt
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-05-03T12:55:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/egyptian-stocks-orascom-telecom-media-al-baraka-bank-egypt.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX30 Index (EGX30)  advanced
0.5 percent to 4,929.24 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo. That
pared the gauge’s decline to 0.1 percent this week.  The following shares were active on the Egyptian Exchange.
Stock symbols follow company names.  Al Baraka Bank Egypt ESC (SAUD)   gained 2 percent, the
most since April 23, to 8.84 Egyptian pounds. The Cairo-based
unit of Bahrain’s Albaraka Banking Group wants to increase its
profit this year by more than 20 percent,  Al Mal  reported,
citing Managing Director Ashraf El Ghamrawy.  Orascom Telecom Media & Technology Holding SAE (OTMT)  , a
Cairo-based mobile-phone company controlled by Egyptian
billionaire  Naguib Sawiris , rose as much as 2.2 percent to 1.41
pounds before closing at 1.39 pounds.  Telecom Italia SpA (TIT) , the
country’s largest phone company, is in talks to sell its Matrix
SpA Internet unit to Sawiris, according to a person with
knowledge of the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
